Contradictory Narratives: A significant line of argument was the highlighting of contradictions within the biblical narrative. Ibn Hazm, for instance, meticulously compared the four Gospel accounts of the calling of the first disciples and the events of the crucifixion, arguing that the discrepancies in timing, location, and sequence of events prove that the texts are the work of human hands and not a perfect divine revelation.
