When the sun is closer to Vishnunabhi, humanity's collective dharma is more developed, leading to an expansion of intellect (buddhi, बुद्धि) and perceptual capacity . When the sun is at its farthest point, dharma is at its nadir, and consciousness is constricted .
Modulation of Consciousness Through the Yugas: The 12,000-year ascending and descending arcs are each composed of four yugas, with specific effects on human perception .
Kali Yuga (Iron Age - 1,200 years): This is the darkest age, when the sun is farthest from the grand center . Human intellect is confined to comprehending only the gross material world . The lowest point of the last Kali Yuga is dated to approximately 499 CE .
