Treta Yuga (Silver Age - 3,600 years): In this age, the human mind gains the power to comprehend divine magnetism, the source of all creative forces .
Satya Yuga (Golden Age - 4,800 years): At the cycle's peak, when the sun is nearest to Vishnunabhi, dharma is fully developed . The human intellect can comprehend all things, including the nature of Spirit itself, which lies beyond creation .
